This paper is about machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of back-translations and pre-training language models, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), making cs.AI and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. The authors also mention studying the impact of vast amounts of data on translation quality, which could fall under neural networks (cs.NE) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
